Using windows command prompt to open pip.exe or easy_install.exe

1. Download the binary packages from the website: 
http://www.lfd.uci.edu/~gohlke/pythonlibs/

File name: 
rpy2-2.5.6-cp27-none-win_amd64.whl

2. Change some system environment variables:

a. For the variable path, add the directory where R executable sits: 
C:\Program Files\R\R-3.2.0\bin\x64
b. Add an R_HOME system variable and set it to the top level directory of my R installation: C:\Program Files\R\R-3.0.2\.
c. Add an R_USER system variable and set it to the directory that the rpy2 module would install into: C:\Anaconda3\Lib\site-packages\rpy2\.
 
3.  Install through the windows command 

a. cd the directory to where the pip.exe sits 

b.  save the whl files downloaded in the same directory as where the pip.exe sits

c. type in the command
 pip install rpy2-2.5.6-cp27-none-win_amd64.whl
